    "description": "Fujimak Corporation engages in the manufacture, sale, maintenance, and repair of commercial kitchen equipment in Japan and internationally. The company offers ovens, teppanyaki grills, fryer oil filters, gas ranges, induction stoves, warmers, griddles, salamander roasters, noodle boilers, rotary cooking kettle braising pans, dumpling grillers, steamers, package cookers, and reheating cabinets, as well as electric ranges, tables, and stock pot ranges; refrigerators, freezers, blast chillers, showcases, cold food carts, ice makers, and vacuum and tabletop coolers; Kitchen Link Cloud, a cloud-based temperature management system; Kitchen Link, a system that centrally manages data; I-Robo2, a stir-fry cooking robot; finibo, a system that automates the picking and sorting cleaned dishes; and island and custom-made home kitchens. It also provides dishwashers, cookware washers, sterilizer cabinets, and ultraviolet sterilizers; cleaning agents for washing machines; carts; automatic rice cookers, storage products, and silos; bakery equipment; cabinets and camshelving equipment; Pacojet, a frozen pulverizing cooker; vacuum packing machines, blenders and mixers, and cookers; gelato/ice cream service equipment, drink dispensers and machines, auxiliary cooking equipment, and water heaters; and sanitary sinks and bars, automatic hand sanitizer dispensers, air showers, electrolyzed water generators, digital probe thermometers, and water softeners and purifiers. The company sells its products online. It serves government agencies and public institutions; educational institutions and school lunch centers; medical and welfare facilities; hotels, inns, and lodging facilities; restaurants and izakayas; amusement facilities; fast food establishments; convenience stores; food processing plants and central kitchens; company cafeterias; ship kitchen facilities; and other industries. Fujimak Corporation was incorporated in 1950 and is headquartered in Minato, Japan."
